			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	Foodtree answers the question: Where is my food from? Whether you are a locavore, concerned about your carbon footprint, have food allergies or want the best quality, Foodtree is a trusted source of reliable and relevant information about food for the millions of consumers who want more information about their food purchases.&nbsp;<br />
	<br />
	Foodtree is searching for a whip-smart database engineer and perhaps a Rails wizard to join their small team.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	Some Details:</p>
<p>
	- The successful candidate will need a high degree of familiarity with Ruby on Rails, SQL, and LAMP development. This is a highly technical, hands-on job so the Development Lead will need to handle all aspects of planning and development for the community.<br />
	- Ideally the lead developer will have worked on a project shepherding an online community from prototype to completion. Experience working with contracted international development teams is very helpful.<br />
	- Candidates with connections to or a background in food are strongly preferred. Did you grow up on a farm? Have you ever worked as a chef?<br />
	- A passion for fixing the food system and a strong desire to make the world a better place are key ingredients to fitting in with the team.<br />
	- This role will require a great deal of high-level communication as it&#39;s a key hire for the company; the candidate will be to expected to work on presentations, conduct meetings, and participate in key decisions.&nbsp;</p>
<p>
	Compensation and benefits commensurate with experience, but likely a combination of cash and equity. Must be able to work in downtown Vancouver.&nbsp;</p>
